this is the unofficial and floating in time roadmap:


Sep 2003:

   - convert passive list to hostlist

   
   + FILTERING ENGINE
      - don't filter in unoffensive mode
      - use regexp for filtering
      - include all the protocols in the filter rule
         - protocols table
         - parsing engine
            - SP (string pointer)
            - FLAGS (flags
      - filter even the header of the packets
      - etterfilter (utility) (used to compile the filter in bytecode)
      

   + MITM METHODS
      - icmp redirect
      - dhcp poisoning
      - port stealing
      
Oct 2003:

   + INJECTION 
      - it is done by the ui looking the sessions (locking them)
      - don't inject in unoffensive mode
      - binder
   
   + DISSECTORS
      - convert all the old dissectors
      - HTTPS without the dirty trick (can we use loopback?)
      - HTTP sniff cookies
      - SSH has to support DES, 3DES, blowfish and zlib compression
      - WIFI decoder support for WEP (key given)
      - PPP decoder
      - DHCP

Nov 2003:

   + PLUGINS
      - convert all the old plugins
      - check for poisoner
      - linktype
      - "active" passive fingerprint

Dec 2003:

   + INTERFACE ENGINE
      - console
      - ncurses
         - configurable colors
      - cursed gtk
         http://zemljanka.sourceforge.net/cursed/
      - gtk
         - redesigned
         - win32 port

   + DEVELOPMENT DOCUMENTATION

   + ETTERLOG
      - extract files from streams looking for mime content

25 Jan 2004:

   + FIRST PUBLIC (pre)RELEASE


